The weather forecast on Saturday, 21 November 2020. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Weather Services is warning of more possible storms and flooding in different parts of the country this weekend. KwaZulu-Natal and Gauteng have been the worst hit by heavy rain this week. A roof collapsed onto several cars at a Vereeniging garage on Friday. READ: Gauteng authorities warn of possible flash flooding In KZN a 22-year-old woman died after she was swept away in a flooding river. The extreme weather warning comes just days after a tornado ripped through Mthatha in the Eastern Cape.